, signed languages can go extinct due to a decrease in the number of deaf individuals (usually related to diversification in the available gene pool of certain communities). This is in contrast to spoken languages, where the majority of language death is not a direct result of the disappearance of a certain group of people. More controversially, signed languages can disappear as a result of eugenic policies and mandates. For example, in Adamorobe (a village in eastern Ghana) a policy was put into place forbidding deaf individuals to marry each other, and as such the deaf population (and subsequently the use of Adamorobe Sign Language) decreased around 10%25  in 50 years. %0a%3c %0a%3c https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adamorobe_Sign_Language%0a%3c https://www.sil.org/system/files/reapdata/12/96/81/129681979560727324424065691676610323327/SignLanguageRevitalizationChapter_author_preprint.pdf%0a%3c https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sign_language#Technology%0a%3c https://www.theguardian.com/news/2016/aug/10/race-to-save-hawaii-sign-language%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c You must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a%3c !!Change article category%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#changearticlecategory:)%0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:Section: E:)%0a%3c (:Category: SignLanguage:)%0a%3c (:Title: Endangerment of Sign Languages